    <h2>UI/UX Case Study</h2>

    <h3>Student Management System Redesign</h3>

    <p><strong>Problem:</strong> Students and administrators often struggle with managing academic records due to complex and non-intuitive systems.</p>

    <p><strong>Goal:</strong> To design a simple, user-friendly interface that allows easy access to student data and improves overall usability.</p>

    <p><strong>My Process:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Identified key users (students and administrators)</li>
        <li>Analyzed usability challenges like navigation complexity</li>
        <li>Designed a clean and structured layout</li>
        <li>Focused on simplicity, accessibility, and visual clarity</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Clean dashboard with organized data</li>
        <li>Simple navigation for ease of use</li>
        <li>Clear layout to reduce confusion</li>
        <li>Consistent color theme inspired by the Vercel “purple pages” for better user engagement</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Result:</strong> Improved usability by making the system easier to navigate and more efficient for users.</p>

    <p><strong>Tools Used:</strong> Java, UI/UX Design Principles</p>

